Prerequisite
============
Lua 5.2 (https://www.lua.org/ftp/)
Python 2.7 (https://www.python.org/downloads/)

Optional (for running tests)
==============================
CppUnit (https://freedesktop.org/wiki/Software/cppunit/)
LuaUnit (https://github.com/bluebird75/luaunit)
PyUnit

Build with Autotools
====================
1. Clone the repository
2. Change to the directory
3. Generate configuration files
   autoreconf -i
4. Download ax_cxx_compile_stdcxx.m4 and move it into directory m4/
   (https://www.gnu.org/software/autoconf-archive/ax_cxx_compile_stdcxx.html)
5. Make a build directory
   (e.g. mkdir _build)
6. Change to the build directory
7. Configure the package
   ../configure
   (run ../configure --help for options)
8. Build and install the package
   make && make install
9. Run tests (optional)
   make check

Build with CMake
================
1. Clone the repository
2. Change to the directory
3. Make a build directory
   (e.g. mkdir _build)
4. Change to the build directory
5. Configure the package
   (e.g. cmake .. -G "Unix Makefiles")
6. Build the package
   make
7. Run tests (optional)
   make check
